<body id="rxtx_control___installation">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">RxTx Control - Installation</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Installation of the <em class="ph i">RxTx Control</em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Insert the new <em class="ph i">RxTx Control</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">With the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Screwdriver
                                        PH2 x 300</span></em>
                    mount and tighten the four screws, which are holding the <em class="ph i">RxTx Control</em> to
                    the back of the cabinet (see red circles in <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Screws">Figure 2</a> and
                        <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Two_Slots">Figure 3</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Use a <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Torque
                                        wrench, 1 Nm</span></em>
                    and an <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Extender for
                                        torque wrench</span></em> to
                    mount and tighten the <em class="ph i">SMA Connectors</em> X1 - X10 (see red circles in <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Connectors">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">With the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Screwdriver
                                        PH2 x 300</span></em>
                    mount the four <em class="ph i">D-Sub Connectors</em> X12, X13, X14 and X15 on the <em class="ph i">RxTx
                        Control</em> (see the four lower red ellipses in <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Connectors">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Mount the <em class="ph i">PCIe Connector</em> X11 on the <em class="ph i">RxTx Control</em> (see item 1 in <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Connectors">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Use a <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Torque
                                        wrench, 1 Nm</span></em>
                    and an <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Extender for
                                        torque wrench</span></em> to
                    mount and tighten the <em class="ph i">SMA Connectors</em> X2 - X9 (see yellow circles in <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___removal.html#rxtx_control___removal__Connectors">Figure 1</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Turn on power to the transceiver with the power switch on the <em class="ph i">PSU</em>.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch “<em class="ph i">Mains On</em>” with the <em class="ph i">Radar Service Application</em> (if needed,
                    select antenna rotation, Tx and profile).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Make a <em class="ph i">PSAT calibration</em> of the SSPA (see <a class="xref" href="cm_rxtx_control___psat_calibration.html#rxtx_control___psat_calibration" title="Calibration of the RxTx Control - PSAT.">RxTx Control - PSAT calibration</a>).</span>
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

